Definitions

"Competing Use" means using the Licensed Work, in whole or in part, to provide
data platform consulting, analytics engineering delivery, or technology advisory
services to third parties where the Licensed Work is used as a delivery
methodology framework — whether or not a fee is charged for those services.

This includes, but is not limited to: using Wire to structure or deliver client
engagements, offering Wire-based delivery packages or accelerators, bundling Wire
within a consulting service offering, or distributing the Licensed Work as part
of a commercial delivery methodology.

This does not include:

  (a) An organisation using the Licensed Work to manage and deliver its own
      internal data platform work, provided that organisation does not offer
      data platform consulting services to third parties as a primary business
      activity.

  (b) Individual contributors submitting bug reports, documentation
      improvements, or code contributions to this repository.

  (c) Academic research, non-commercial education, or evaluation for the
      purpose of determining whether to engage Rittman Analytics Ltd.

